	<p>Body mass index is obtained by dividing your body weight by the square of your height. As a result, the body mass index is evaluated in the following intervals.
	</p>

	<h6 class="font-weight-bold">Weak</h6>

	<p>Indicates that you are not in the proper weight according to your height and that you are weak. Weakness is a risky and undesirable condition for some diseases. You should be well-balanced and balanced to reach the appropriate weight for your height and take care to improve your eating habits.</p>
	<h6 class="font-weight-bold">Normal</h6>

	<p>Indicates that you have the appropriate weight according to your height. Take care to protect your weight by having adequate and balanced nutrition and regular physical activity.</p>
	<h6 class="font-weight-bold">Overweight</h6>

	<p>Indicates your body weight is higher than your height. Overweight leads to obesity (obesity), which is a risk factor for many diseases unless the necessary precautions are taken.</p>
